Class Summary
BonusHole This class creates a game piece which asks the user a bonus question when a penguin lands on it.
CrackedIce A GamePiece that acts as an obstacle.
DisplayHighScores This class displays the top ten scores to the user and contains a button to print them, a button to clear them and a button to return to the main menu.
EndGame This creates several labels and a textfield as well as buttons which will display the user's score after they have completed the game and store their username.
FishingHole This class creates a game piece which asks the user a general biology question when a penguin lands on it.
GamePiece An entity in the game represented by an image.
Goodbye The screen that displays when the user wants to exit the program.
HighScores This sorts and outputs the top 10 highest game scores and according usernames into a file.
Instructions This creates several labels and a button which will output the instructions and allow the user to return to the main menu once they have finished reading them.
Learn Screen that displays information the user should study.
LevelSelect This create a labels and buttons which allow the user to select from either easy medium or hard game levels.
MainMenu The main menu screen of the game allows the user to navigate throughout the program.
MarchOfThePenguinsApp The driver starts the game by calling the frame.
Penguin The game piece that the player controls.
PenguinBoard The game board where the game occurs.
PenguinFrame The Frame for the program that contains the screens, tool bars and menus.
PlayGame The screen where the user plays the game.
Printer Helper class designed to make printing easier.
Screen A screen in the game.
Seal An enemy GamePiece that resembles a Seal.
Skua An enemy game piece representing the Skua bird.
SplashScreen The program's splash screen that displays when you first start the program.
